<p><strong>CRH</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>DMN, PVN, VMN</li>
<li>41 aa , very lage</li>
<li>diumal pattern of release</li>
<li>stimulator of ACTH and b-endorphin</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>TRH</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>DMN, VMN, PVN, ARC, PVa</li>
<li>also neuromodulator in ANS</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>GnRH</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>ARC, FOA, ah</li>
<li>pulsatile</li>
<li>increase release of FSH, LH</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>GHRH</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>44aa</li>
<li>increase  GH </li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Dopamine</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>inhibitor of prolactin release</li>
<li>release of MSH</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Somatostatin</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>POA, ah, DMN, VMN, Arc, PVa</li>
<li>inhibit release of GH, TSH, PRL (act mostly as inhibitor of secretion)</li>
<li>antagonist to GHRH, TRH </li>
<li>widespread throughout the brain outside hypothalamus and periphery. </li>
</ul>
	
